Peters was wearing a white and yellow T-shirt with blue shorts, and was barefoot at the time of her disappearance. She has brown eyes and medium-length, dark brown hair which was braided in two plaits and tied with baubles. Statistics released by Missing Children SA this week showed the organisation saw an increase in cases between May 1, 2016 and April 30 this year. A total of 304 adults and 181 children were reported missing nationally during that time. Of those, 167 adults and 145 children were found.